<h2 id="project-management">Project Management: Monday.com -- $9-19/seat/mo</h2>

Opening a new franchise unit involves 50-100+ tasks across construction, permitting, equipment, hiring, training, marketing launch, and technology setup. Without a centralized project management system, tasks fall through cracks and openings get delayed.

Monday.com works for franchise operations because of its template system. Build a master "New Unit Opening" board with every task, dependency, and timeline. When a new franchise signs, duplicate the board and assign owners. Every opening follows the same playbook.

The visual timeline view lets corporate track all active openings simultaneously. Which units are on schedule? Which are delayed? Where are the bottlenecks? That visibility is worth the subscription.

<p><strong>Cost:</strong> $9/seat/mo for Basic, $19/seat/mo for Pro with automations and integrations.</p>

